The Institute The mission of the Institute of Cognitive Science (ICS) is to promote interdisciplinary research in the cognitive sciences. Faculty and research professionals in ICS are drawn from various departments including Psychology, Philosophy, Computer Science, Linguistics, Education, and Communications. The research in the Institute can be broadly classified into four areas: human-computer interaction (HCI) and knowledge-based systems, natural language processing, information processing and skilled performance, and judgement and decision making. This review will summarize ICS research efforts in HCI and knowledge-based systems.